s in both China and the former Soviet Union. Microsoft sold its DOS to China and Russia during the Reagan administration along with Windows (which carrried on through the Bush administration). That's just starters.<br><br>[quote]"4) Suddenly any businessman or corporation is totally ethicless, money grubbing, and just plain old greedy? For some reason being a capitalist is an evil thing?"[/quote]<br><br>Did I say that? Let me take a look... nope it wasn't me.<br><br>[quote]"5) If WE dismantle our bio/chem warefare arsenal, it would honestly not bother me. However, I do not see the arsenal of U.S. bio/chem weapons becoming a terrorist threat to the world at large. Iraq's has a strong possibility of such and thus IS our and the world's business. That is the difference."[/quote]<br><br>You are still not admitting to the issue of the sovereignty of each nation. You want to keep thinking that the USA is somehow above and beyond all other nation states so we are above world law. It is not about terrorists attacks... it is about violating the sovereignty of another country. Would you like another country to invade US sovereignty? Time to lay aside the hypocrisy and admit it is wrong. <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>Necromancer <BR>Proud Member of <a href="http://magustytalus.tripod.com/">The Order of Magus Tytalus</a><BR><BR>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulithahntalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lith Ahntalon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/16/02 3:00:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left cla