ust a little over 10 years ago Iraq LOST a war and the current leadership is there only by the good graces of the world community, a community that could have and should have (in my opinion) removed thier leadership while we had the chance. Taking all this into account I think it IS the worlds business to ensure thier bio/chem weapons program does not get off the ground. Short of sending an armed force back in there and forcibly doing it, Iraq is getting off light.  <p><img src=http://eshamlin.home.mindspring.com/lith.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 426<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/16/02 11:47:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;In the case of Iraq, it's leadership has shown itself to be aggressive to other nations (read invading and brutally occupying another nation with no intentions to leave), cruel and deadly to segments of it's own population (read using weapons of mass destruction on it's own population to maitain political power), and engaged in a weapons of mass destruction program. Yea, that is the neighbor I want in the world community. Further, just a little over 10 years ago Iraq LOST a war and the current leadership is there only by the good graces of the world community, a community that could have and should have (in my opinion) removed thier leadership while we had the chance.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Lith, Iraq  has only been aggressive towards two nations in the last 100 years: Iran and Kuwait. The USA was all to happy to help Iraq in its war against Iran. S h i t, we trained their troops and supplied them with arms and the technology they currently have in order to defeat Iran. (Hmm... it was Nixon who started to give them that technology, btw. Just thought you should know.) If Iraq is truly a threat to world peace then so is Butt F u c k Egypt. Furthermore, the leadership in Iraq is there by the sheer will of the Hussein family. Saddam Hussein is a totalitarian and prides himself as a follower of Stalinism. The world community could not destroy him without defeating the nation itself. <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>Necromancer <BR>Proud Member of <a href="http://magustytalus.tripod.com/">The Order of Magus Tytalus</a><BR><BR>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulithahntalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lith Ahntalon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 257<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/20/02 7:25:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> I disagree. We had the ability to take out Saddam during the Gulf War and chose not to ( a fact I still lament ). He is there only through the good graces of the world as a whole. I am sure a scenario that was just recently completed in Afganistan would see a good amount of succes in Iraq if applied. I will admit Bush Sr. 