intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/21/02 5:33:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> Think you have it wrong Ritt. True enough, only time will tell but, we do have success stories with defeated nations, Germany and Japan come to mind and I quite frankly think you underestimate people. <p><img src=http://eshamlin.home.mindspring.com/lith.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaphroditex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphroditex</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/21/02 6:17:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> 1) When the US sends letters filled with biochemical weapons to you in your daily mail delivery then you can talk about who should be forced to dismantle their bio/chem warfare factories. Have we done this to you? No? Then nuff said.<br><br><br><br>2) Selling other countries 3rd and 4th generation weaponry that we most like (a) have a new and better version of or (b) have a way to detect easily, is FAR FAR different than letting the world at large learn of our most technologically advanced biochemical weapons, which have never been used for terrorist purposes in other countries. Again, when you can show me proof (even a tiny shread) that we used our biochem weapons in this way, you can dictate whether we should distroy our chem weapons. Until then I prefer our country working on them as much as possible so that when your countries (read those countries in the middle east that you find so precious) come up with the damn things and let them loose on us we will have already had 10 years advance notice to work on them and develop a treatment and cure.<br><br><br>I think that just about covers it, and for the record I'm not affiliated with a party nor do I wish to be placed into a stereotype. <p><b><i>Your resident troll</i></b><BR>Aphroditex Bubblefists;  Serenity Z'Chaotic; Pickett Pocketts<BR>Human <a href><font color="#66FF00"><b>Master</b></font></a>;            Dark Elf <a href><font color=red><b>Channeler</b></font></a>; Halfling Rogue<BR><a href><font color=#FF7000><b>Member of Anlah'shok</b></font></a><BR><a href><font color=#FFCC00><i>"We walk in the dark places no one will enter, we stand on the bridge and no one may pass, we live for the one, we die for the one."</i></font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urittdabard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rittdabard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/21/02 7:19:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> Lith, I never considered Germany or Japan 3rd world. In fact even when they were our enemies they had much more stable leadership than Afgahnistan does now.<br><br>Aphroditex, don't read the news much? The anthrax attacks I believe you are inferring to were domestic. Last report said that suspect number one had FBI ties. Well the U.S. government does not own up to its actions with what it does with Bio/Chem weapons that's the point. However some years later we learned of the Tuskegee experiments. Does that qualify as the U.S. using bio-tech on its own people, or is that just simple disease research? I think what it was isn't as important however as the ethics behind such an operation. <br><br>Ritt<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulithahntalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lith Ahntalon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/21/02 7:27:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue state threat to world security?</span><hr size=1> Never said they were third world countries but, if you want to push it, they might as well have been after the war. Thier infrastructre was shot, in the case of Japan there was a  large if not total overhaul of thier politcial and idealogical system, and an almost total rebuild of the nation(s) were required. <p><img src=http://eshamlin.home.mindspring.com/lith.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/21/02 10:19:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>